  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims to assess whether the electrical signal of the diaphragm (diaphragm
      electromyogram) and the ratio of that to tidal volume (amount of air breathed in and out of
      the lungs) can predict which infants will be successfully extubated (have the breathing tube
      removed without needing it replaced.)
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
